          <p class="lead">An <strong>HVAC maintenance plan</strong> is the best way to protect your heating and cooling investment. Latour's HVAC maintenance plans include annual tune-ups for both your AC and heating system, plus priority scheduling, repair discounts, and peace of mind knowing your system is in top condition.</p>

          <p>Louisiana's climate is tough on HVAC equipment. Your AC runs almost constantly from April through October, and humidity challenges your system year-round. Regular maintenance isn't a luxury—it's essential for reliable operation and reasonable energy bills.</p>

          <h2>What's Included in Our Maintenance Plans</h2>

          <h3>Two Complete Tune-Ups Per Year</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Spring AC Tune-Up:</strong> Comprehensive inspection and service before cooling season</li>
            <li><strong>Fall Heating Tune-Up:</strong> Complete check of your furnace or heat pump before winter</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Plan Member Benefits</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Priority Scheduling:</strong> Skip the wait during busy seasons—plan members go to the front of the line</li>
            <li><strong>15% Repair Discount:</strong> Save on any repairs needed throughout the year</li>
            <li><strong>No Overtime Charges:</strong> Same rate for evenings and weekends</li>
            <li><strong>Reminder Service:</strong> We'll contact you when it's time to schedule</li>
            <li><strong>Transferable:</strong> Adds value if you sell your home</li>
            <li><strong>Peace of Mind:</strong> Know your system is being professionally maintained</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Benefits of Regular HVAC Maintenance</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Prevent Breakdowns:</strong> 80% of HVAC failures could be prevented with regular maintenance. Tune-ups catch small problems before they become big repairs.</li>
            <li><strong>Lower Energy Bills:</strong> A clean, tuned system operates 15-25% more efficiently than a neglected one.</li>
            <li><strong>Extend Equipment Life:</strong> Well-maintained systems last 15-20 years vs. 10-12 years for neglected equipment.</li>
            <li><strong>Maintain Warranty:</strong> Most manufacturer warranties require annual professional maintenance.</li>
            <li><strong>Better Air Quality:</strong> Clean coils and fresh filters mean cleaner air for your family.</li>
            <li><strong>Consistent Comfort:</strong> Properly maintained systems keep temperatures more even.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>What We Check During Tune-Ups</h2>

          <h3>Cooling Season (AC Tune-Up)</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Clean condenser and evaporator coils</li>
            <li>Check refrigerant levels and pressures</li>
            <li>Inspect and tighten electrical connections</li>
            <li>Test capacitors and contactors</li>
            <li>Lubricate moving parts</li>
            <li>Check thermostat calibration</li>
            <li>Clear condensate drain</li>
            <li>Replace or clean air filter</li>
            <li>Test system operation and temperatures</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Heating Season (Furnace/Heat Pump Tune-Up)</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Inspect heat exchanger (gas furnaces)</li>
            <li>Check burner operation and gas pressure</li>
            <li>Test safety controls</li>
            <li>Check defrost cycle (heat pumps)</li>
            <li>Inspect electrical connections</li>
            <li>Test thermostat operation</li>
            <li>Check flue and venting</li>
            <li>Replace or clean air filter</li>
            <li>Test system operation</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Why Maintenance Matters in Louisiana</h2>
          <p>Lake Charles' climate puts extra demands on HVAC systems:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Long Cooling Season:</strong> Your AC runs 7+ months per year</li>
            <li><strong>High Humidity:</strong> Systems work harder to remove moisture</li>
            <li><strong>Gulf Air:</strong> Salt and humidity accelerate corrosion</li>
            <li><strong>Storm Debris:</strong> Outdoor units need regular cleaning</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Regular maintenance addresses these challenges and keeps your system performing its best.</p>

